OL,3,CMerseyside prisons top list of most
OL,4,Cinmates released early say new figures
OL,6,FAccording to the MoJ this "sharp rise"
OL,7,Fin quarterly recalls is "likely to be
OL,8,Fassociated with the increase in
OL,9,Freleases" following the introduction
OL,10,Fof the ECSL scheme in October 2023.
OL,12,FThere can be more than one reason for
OL,13,Frecalling an offender on licence - for
OL,14,Fexample, of the 9,782 recalls in the
OL,15,Fthree months to June 2024, 77%
OL,16,Finvolved non-compliance with
OL,17,Fconditions, 36% involved failing to
OL,18,Fkeep in touch and 24% involved a
OL,19,Fcharge of further offending.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
